
[1]laureation

   LAUREA'TION, n. The act of conferring a degree in the university,
   together with a wreath of laurel; an honor bestowed on those who
   excelled in writing verse. This was an ancient practice at Oxford, from
   which probably originated the denomination of poet laureate.
